==Ancient Germanic ==
===Etymology===
Means "ruler of the people" from the Germanic elements þeud "people" and ric "power". 

===Namesake===
Theodoric the Great was a 6th-century king of the Ostrogoths who eventually became the ruler of Italy.

===Pronounced===
the-AHD-o-rik

